  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: Clients: *1.8.12-stable-37685930* and *1.8.11-stable-dea1ce05*, Server: *1.8.12-stable-37685930*.  Tested on various combos of above.\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu and Arch Linux\r\nCommit hash : n/a\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhisper message transmission\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\nINFO [07-12|21:10:39.358] message loop peer=0fa67975aabc693c err=EOF\r\n```\r\nNo message is transmitted.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nA public geth node is set up - currently live here: `addr = \"enode://0fa67975aabc693c6fafde2b216b0a2c5c51da130d210ec74c045b4526e5f67050d04c3ac2445e1e106f15d2caf62d82ec8e640a57f6aee036b816c46d9963c4@35.203.151.98:30303\"`, running `geth --shh --syncmode light --datadir /eth/data --port 30303`.  \r\n\r\nThe enode address is called with admin.addPeer(addr).  Code is run to relay a test message:\r\n\r\n**receiver**\r\nid = shh.generateSymKeyFromPassword('foobar')\r\ncb = function(error, messages){console.log(\"RECEIVED MESSAGE\", JSON.stringify(messages))}\r\nf = shh.newMessageFilter({topics: ['0x07678231'], symKeyID: id}, cb)\r\n\r\n**sender**\r\nid = shh.generateSymKeyFromPassword('foobar')\r\nshh.post({ttl: 700, topic: '0x07678231', powTarget: 2.01, powTime: 2, payload: '0x68656c6c6f', symKeyID: id})\r\n\r\nBut the only apparent behavior is a recurring error message as above (message loop..EOF) every so often.  The only configuration that does work is the non-relaying case of the sender and receiver being the same geth console.\r\n\r\nOnly firewall opening on public geth node above was to allow TCP 30303.  I imagine that's not the problem, but bears mentioning.",
